WEBVTT

00:01.251 --> 00:03.544
[theme music playing]

00:13.634 --> 00:15.435
<i> One, two!
One, two, three, four!</i>

00:15.435 --> 00:19.189
<i> ♪ La la la la la la la la ♪</i>

00:23.023 --> 00:25.816
<i> ♪ La la la la la ♪</i>

00:28.198 --> 00:29.610
[chicken squawks]

00:33.614 --> 00:36.116
Okay, I've got
one soy latte for you,

00:36.116 --> 00:38.078
one iced cappuccino over here,

00:38.078 --> 00:40.921
aaand Parade Day necklaces
for everyone!

00:40.921 --> 00:42.252
-Whoo!
-All right!

00:42.252 --> 00:43.253
Happy Parade Day, y'all!

00:43.253 --> 00:45.716
Thank you, sir, and have
a happy Parade Day.

00:45.716 --> 00:47.047
-[doorbell jingles]
- Enjoy it.

00:47.047 --> 00:48.258
Some of us can't be there,

00:48.258 --> 00:50.130
even though
we really want to be...

00:50.130 --> 00:51.301
just once.

00:51.301 --> 00:52.843
Happy Parade Day,
Gloria! Ehh!

00:52.843 --> 00:54.264
Whee!

00:54.264 --> 00:55.475
So when are we goin'
to the parade?

00:55.475 --> 00:58.228
Uh, we can't go
to the parade.

00:58.228 --> 01:00.480
This is the cafe's
busiest day of the year.

01:00.480 --> 01:02.232
Well, surely, work
allows you to do fun stuff

01:02.232 --> 01:03.734
when there's fun stuff
to do.

01:03.734 --> 01:05.606
[scoffs] Look, I want
to see the parade, too.

01:05.606 --> 01:08.148
but it's our responsibility
to stay here

01:08.148 --> 01:09.950
and keep the cafe running.

01:09.950 --> 01:11.952
So since we're
in this together,

01:11.952 --> 01:13.954
I suggest you quit whining

01:13.954 --> 01:15.996
and go take out
the trash.

01:15.996 --> 01:17.998
Fine! But I want
my beads back!

01:17.998 --> 01:19.159
No.
They look good on me.

01:19.159 --> 01:20.751
-[doorbell jingles]
-[Bill] Hey, Cricket!

01:20.751 --> 01:22.042
We're headed
over to the parade.

01:22.042 --> 01:24.204
-You joinin' us?
-No, I can't.

01:24.204 --> 01:25.375
I gotta stay here
and work.

01:25.375 --> 01:27.167
Aw, that's a shame.

01:27.167 --> 01:29.379
We've watched the parade
on TV every year.

01:29.379 --> 01:31.592
This year, we actually
get to see it in person!

01:31.592 --> 01:34.264
And it's all happenin'
just a block away from here!

01:34.264 --> 01:36.176
It's so convenient!

01:36.176 --> 01:38.268
Plus, you're gonna miss
seein' me on a float.

01:38.268 --> 01:40.310
Uh, no, Tilly.

01:40.310 --> 01:42.182
We're just gonna
watch the parade.

01:42.182 --> 01:43.894
We're not gonna be in it.

01:43.894 --> 01:46.356
If you say so.

01:46.356 --> 01:48.689
[laughs] Oh, listen to us
ramble on and on.

01:48.689 --> 01:50.280
We're keepin' you
from your work.

01:50.280 --> 01:52.192
Have a good day, son!

01:52.192 --> 01:54.154
It won't be the same
without you,

01:54.154 --> 01:56.496
but it will still be
very, very fun!

01:56.496 --> 01:57.908
Bye!

01:57.908 --> 01:59.199
Mm-mm!

01:59.199 --> 02:01.161
I gotta get to that parade!

02:01.161 --> 02:03.413
Stupid job ain't gonna
keep me from watchin' it!

02:03.413 --> 02:04.955
Gotta find a way
to sneak outta work

02:04.955 --> 02:06.336
with Gloria catchin' me.

02:06.336 --> 02:08.048
But how?

02:08.048 --> 02:11.842
Cricket, go take the trash
out to the dumpster!

02:11.842 --> 02:13.423
Hmmm...

02:13.423 --> 02:15.305
Sure thing, Gloria.

02:15.305 --> 02:18.258
I'll be riiight back.

02:18.258 --> 02:20.310
Hmm...

02:20.310 --> 02:22.432
[grunting]

02:22.432 --> 02:24.314
[whistling]

02:26.266 --> 02:28.438
-[knocks on glass]
-Hey! You better not be
tryin' to sneak off

02:28.438 --> 02:29.609
to watch the parade!

02:29.609 --> 02:30.861
Ohh!

02:30.861 --> 02:32.112
Mmm...

02:32.112 --> 02:34.274
Whoa-oa-oof!

02:34.274 --> 02:36.076
Oh, what was that?!

02:36.076 --> 02:38.368
You desperately need
more napkins?!

02:38.368 --> 02:40.370
I'll go get some
right away, sir!

02:40.370 --> 02:42.332
I didn't ask for napkins.

02:42.332 --> 02:43.664
Okay, relax,
I'm gettin' you

02:43.664 --> 02:45.666
all those napkins
you asked for!

02:45.666 --> 02:47.457
[sighs]

02:47.457 --> 02:48.378
[chuckles]

02:48.378 --> 02:50.420
Now, where
are those napkins?!

02:50.420 --> 02:51.421
[chuckling]

02:51.421 --> 02:52.382
Too easy.

02:53.794 --> 02:56.296
Aha! Parade here I come!

02:56.296 --> 02:57.678
Ohh!

02:57.678 --> 02:59.639
Back inside... now!

02:59.639 --> 03:01.261
Mmm...

03:01.261 --> 03:03.974
-Now!
-Mm-mm!

03:03.974 --> 03:05.896
Thank you and have
a happy Parade Day.

03:05.896 --> 03:07.808
Now where did Cricket go?

03:07.808 --> 03:10.861
Umph! Dang it!
I was so close!

03:10.861 --> 03:12.522
Maybe if I sneak out
through the vents...

03:12.522 --> 03:15.866
That's it!
You're on mop duty
for the rest of the day!

03:17.487 --> 03:19.529
Ah, stupid Gloria
and her responsibilities

03:19.529 --> 03:21.451
rainin' on my Parade Day!

03:21.451 --> 03:24.374
Huh? 15-minute break?

03:24.374 --> 03:25.495
That's it!

03:25.495 --> 03:26.326
Loophole!

03:26.326 --> 03:27.748
Loophole!
Loophole! Loophole!

03:27.748 --> 03:29.499
Habeas corpus!
I object!

03:29.499 --> 03:30.290
What now?

03:30.290 --> 03:32.382
According to the law,

03:32.382 --> 03:34.134
I get a mandatory
15-minute break,

03:34.134 --> 03:37.387
which I'll be taking
right now to go
watch the parade.

03:37.387 --> 03:38.969
But the rush
is about to start,

03:38.969 --> 03:40.801
so it's not a good time
for your break.

03:40.801 --> 03:43.303
Sorry, Gloria, but for once
the law is on<i> my</i> side.

03:43.303 --> 03:45.055
I'll watch the parade
for a bit

03:45.055 --> 03:46.056
-and be back before
you know it.
-[ticking]

03:46.056 --> 03:47.517
Okay. Okay, fine.

03:47.517 --> 03:49.349
But if you're
not back in 15 minutes,

03:49.349 --> 03:50.400
you're fired!

03:50.400 --> 03:52.062
See ya in 15!

03:52.062 --> 03:54.524
[people chattering]

03:54.524 --> 03:56.066
Oh, my gosh!

03:56.066 --> 03:57.697
Pff! I'll show her!

03:57.697 --> 03:59.489
I'll watch the parade
<i> and</i> keep my job!

03:59.489 --> 04:02.322
Wow! this is a great spot!

04:02.322 --> 04:04.574
It would be
if I could see anything!

04:04.574 --> 04:06.166
Oh, hello, family!

04:06.166 --> 04:07.457
Cricket,
what are you doin' here?

04:07.457 --> 04:09.169
Did Gloria let you
take the day off?

04:09.169 --> 04:11.131
Psh! No! Just takin'
my break early.

04:11.131 --> 04:14.004
I've got 15 minutes
to enjoy as much
of the parade as possible.

04:14.004 --> 04:16.586
Er, well,
more like nine minutes.

04:16.586 --> 04:18.178
You're timin'
is impeccable.

04:18.178 --> 04:19.880
The parade
is about to begin.

04:19.880 --> 04:22.012
Here comes
the Splish Soda float now!

04:22.012 --> 04:24.344
And atop it rides
Miss Splish,

04:24.344 --> 04:26.306
the queen of all sodas.

04:26.306 --> 04:27.557
Ooh!

04:27.557 --> 04:28.809
Ow!

04:28.809 --> 04:30.560
[playing march]

04:30.560 --> 04:34.564
[sound of band playing
grows faint]

04:34.564 --> 04:37.237
Aw! Look how slow
and tiny they are!

04:37.237 --> 04:38.568
At this rate, I won't
get to see anything

04:38.568 --> 04:40.570
-before I have to go back.
-[ticking]

04:40.570 --> 04:43.113
If only there was a way
to watch the parade
from the cafe.

04:43.113 --> 04:44.905
Hmm! Wait a minute!

04:44.905 --> 04:47.537
Loophole! Loophole, loophole,
double loophole!

04:47.537 --> 04:49.079
Tilly, we're gonna
re-route the parade

04:49.079 --> 04:50.540
so that it marches
right past the cafe!

04:50.540 --> 04:51.711
You down to help me?

04:51.711 --> 04:53.213
Always am.

04:53.213 --> 04:55.545
Just gotta finish
my giant lollipop first.

04:58.468 --> 05:00.090
Tilly, I'm on the clock!

05:02.382 --> 05:03.804
Okay, Tilly,
here's the plan.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.186
Officer Keys is guarding
those barricades up ahead.

05:06.186 --> 05:09.019
I need you distract him
so I can sneak past,

05:09.019 --> 05:10.230
adjust the first barricade,

05:10.230 --> 05:11.521
then the second barricade,

05:11.521 --> 05:12.983
and then head back
to the cafe

05:12.983 --> 05:15.275
where I can enjoy
the parade while working,

05:15.275 --> 05:16.276
and Gloria will be
all like,

05:16.276 --> 05:17.938
"Oh, Cricket,
you're so cool!

05:17.938 --> 05:19.649
I'm sorry
I ever doubted ya!"
[chuckles]

05:19.649 --> 05:21.281
Think you can handle
the distraction, Tilly?

05:21.281 --> 05:23.613
Hmm...

05:23.613 --> 05:24.825
Leave it to me.

05:24.825 --> 05:27.077
[humming happily]

05:27.077 --> 05:29.579
Happy Parade Day, officer.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.832
Would you be a dear
and take a photo

05:31.832 --> 05:34.584
of me and my sweet fiancé?

05:34.584 --> 05:36.546
Ain't he a charmer?

05:36.546 --> 05:38.588
Aww! Well, sure thing!

05:38.588 --> 05:39.960
You two make
a cute couple!

05:39.960 --> 05:41.381
-[click]
-Thanks!

05:41.381 --> 05:44.174
We're elopin'
and can never return home.

05:44.174 --> 05:45.635
-[camera clicking]
-Aww! [chuckles]

05:45.635 --> 05:48.018
We're on our honeymoon
right now!

05:48.018 --> 05:49.019
Wow!

05:49.019 --> 05:51.641
Be sure to get
my good side. Uh-huh.

05:51.641 --> 05:53.273
Ha ha!

05:53.273 --> 05:54.524
-[clicks]
-Got it!

05:54.524 --> 05:55.976
These are gonna
come out great!

05:55.976 --> 05:57.647
Ma'am? Ma'am?!

05:57.647 --> 05:59.239
You forgot your camera!

05:59.239 --> 06:00.740
Ma'am-- Sir?

06:00.740 --> 06:02.242
Sir?!

06:02.242 --> 06:04.284
Huh! Love is a mystery.

06:04.284 --> 06:06.326
-[band playing]
-Oh! Here come the parade!

06:06.326 --> 06:07.537
All right, everybody!
This way!

06:07.537 --> 06:09.539
This way!

06:09.539 --> 06:11.291
All good so far, Tilly.

06:11.291 --> 06:12.662
Just gotta
move this barricade,

06:12.662 --> 06:13.914
and then we're home free!

06:13.914 --> 06:17.667
[tires screeching]

06:17.667 --> 06:19.089
Oh, no! My barricades!

06:19.089 --> 06:21.381
The only thing
they couldn't stop

06:21.381 --> 06:24.594
was me! [sobbing]

06:24.594 --> 06:25.886
Aw, come on!

06:25.886 --> 06:27.057
Huh?

06:27.057 --> 06:28.348
[band playing]

06:28.348 --> 06:30.220
[Cricket] Oh, no.

06:30.220 --> 06:31.811
This is not good!

06:31.811 --> 06:33.183
This is not good.

06:33.183 --> 06:34.184
I've been waiting
for so long!

06:34.184 --> 06:35.515
Hey!
Where's my coffee?

06:35.515 --> 06:37.357
Free coffee, please.

06:37.357 --> 06:39.149
My tea has water in it!

06:39.149 --> 06:43.073
Excuse me? Something
happened in the bathroom!

06:43.073 --> 06:44.524
Aah!

06:44.524 --> 06:46.907
You better not be late,
Cricket!

06:46.907 --> 06:48.528
Aw, man,
only five minutes left!

06:48.528 --> 06:50.620
Hey, no problem, no problem!

06:50.620 --> 06:52.242
Hmm...

06:52.242 --> 06:53.243
New plan.

06:53.243 --> 06:54.874
Due to unforeseen circumstances

06:54.874 --> 06:56.296
that were not my fault,

06:56.296 --> 06:57.707
we're gonna have to take
a little detour

06:57.707 --> 06:59.129
through the department store.

06:59.129 --> 07:01.711
[Tilly] Another boffo plan,
Cricket!

07:01.711 --> 07:03.173
♪♪

07:03.173 --> 07:05.505
[music stops]

07:05.505 --> 07:06.716
What should we do?

07:06.716 --> 07:08.508
Hmm, well,
as the parade leader,

07:08.508 --> 07:10.220
-I say..
-Bingo bango!

07:10.220 --> 07:11.511
This way, fellas!

07:11.511 --> 07:12.932
-Hey!
-Sorry, Gerald,

07:12.932 --> 07:14.514
but parade law states
that we must follow

07:14.514 --> 07:17.317
whoever wields the baton,
no matter what.

07:17.317 --> 07:19.609
-But I--
-No matter what!

07:19.609 --> 07:22.562
-[playing cadence]
-[sighs] I understand.

07:22.562 --> 07:24.614
[band playing]

07:24.614 --> 07:25.945
Make way! Make way!

07:25.945 --> 07:27.447
Parade comin' through!

07:27.447 --> 07:29.329
Did that little boy
say para--

07:29.329 --> 07:30.570
Oh, my gosh!

07:30.570 --> 07:32.242
-Here comes Crabby Tabby!
-[balloon creaking]

07:32.242 --> 07:34.914
everyone's
favorite finicky feline!

07:34.914 --> 07:37.077
[man] Wow! Could this day
get any better?

07:37.077 --> 07:38.418
-Oh, yeah! Whoo!
-[laughing]

07:38.418 --> 07:40.750
[both screaming]

07:40.750 --> 07:42.542
Ohh!

07:42.542 --> 07:44.214
Aah!

07:44.214 --> 07:47.177
Tell my wife I love parades!

07:47.177 --> 07:49.469
Nooo!

07:51.141 --> 07:53.093
Hellooo! [nervous laugh]

07:53.093 --> 07:56.186
What on earth is going on?

07:56.186 --> 07:58.098
A revolution.

07:58.098 --> 08:02.102
[chuckles] I can't believe
this is actually working.

08:02.102 --> 08:04.024
-Almost there!
-[muffled music continues]

08:04.024 --> 08:05.485
<i> ♪ Do-do-doo ♪</i>

08:05.485 --> 08:07.237
Can't beat shoppin'
on Parade Day.

08:07.237 --> 08:08.488
The stores are so quiet.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.779
Aah!

08:09.779 --> 08:11.951
Ha ha! All right!
I did it!

08:11.951 --> 08:13.663
The parade's on track.

08:13.663 --> 08:16.036
Now I just gotta
get back to the cafe in...

08:16.036 --> 08:17.497
30 seconds?!

08:17.497 --> 08:18.618
I'm never gonna make it!

08:20.670 --> 08:22.502
[Tilly]
Worry not, Cricket!

08:22.502 --> 08:26.005
A queen always provides
for her people!

08:26.005 --> 08:28.718
Tilly?
Where's Miss Splish?

08:28.718 --> 08:30.090
Oh, she was unfit to rule.

08:30.090 --> 08:31.681
Now grab hold, brother!

08:31.681 --> 08:33.303
Okay!

08:33.303 --> 08:34.684
Here you go!
You can have this back!

08:34.684 --> 08:37.307
Yes! My life
has meaning again!

08:37.307 --> 08:39.229
[grunts] Got it!

08:42.142 --> 08:46.856
Whoa! Aaaah!

08:46.856 --> 08:48.318
Go free, genie!

08:48.318 --> 08:52.282
You are no longer bound
by the whims of man.

08:52.282 --> 08:53.573
Well, back to work.

08:53.573 --> 08:55.415
-Unh!
-[woman] Ow!

08:55.415 --> 08:56.996
Aaah!

08:56.996 --> 08:58.038
I'm gonna make it!

08:58.038 --> 09:01.121
Ow! [grunting]

09:01.121 --> 09:02.662
Ha-cha! Nothin' broken!

09:02.662 --> 09:03.753
-[squeaking]
-Huh?

09:04.754 --> 09:07.127
There he goes.

09:07.127 --> 09:08.668
Thank you
for your service, genie.

09:08.668 --> 09:10.380
-[timer rings]
-Whoa! Gotta go!

09:11.761 --> 09:14.554
Yeah! I did it!
I made it back in time!

09:14.554 --> 09:17.637
I told you I could do it,
Glori...uhhh, oh!

09:17.637 --> 09:18.768
[people arguing]

09:18.768 --> 09:20.730
Oh oh! [groans]

09:20.730 --> 09:23.273
-[man] I want it now!
-Yeesh!

09:23.273 --> 09:25.105
I want to speak
to your manager!

09:25.105 --> 09:27.397
Oh, my gosh! This all happened
in 15 minutes?!

09:27.397 --> 09:29.779
Would you like
whipped cream with that?

09:29.779 --> 09:31.401
Gloria, I'm back.

09:31.401 --> 09:33.283
Oh. Hello, Cricket.

09:33.283 --> 09:34.654
How was your break?

09:34.654 --> 09:36.156
Look, I'm sorry.
I'm startin' to think

09:36.156 --> 09:39.119
it might've been wrong
to leave the cafe when I did.

09:39.119 --> 09:42.292
I guess I was
a pretty lousy co-worker.

09:42.292 --> 09:44.164
Is this what
responsibility feels like?

09:44.164 --> 09:45.795
Ech! It's awful!

09:45.795 --> 09:48.047
Ha! Yeah, it is.

09:48.047 --> 09:49.919
Don't worry,
you'll grow into it.

09:49.919 --> 09:52.212
Um, hello?! Are you
just gonna sit there?!

09:52.212 --> 09:54.134
Papa needs
his macchiato!

09:54.134 --> 09:56.216
Okay, sir. Just a minute.

09:56.216 --> 09:57.887
No, Gloria!
You've done enough!

09:57.887 --> 10:00.059
You've pushed yourself
too hard!

10:00.059 --> 10:03.483
But, Cricket, someone
has to handle these...
monsters!

10:03.483 --> 10:05.985
[customers shouting]

10:05.985 --> 10:08.488
[man]
I have a cappuccino!

10:08.488 --> 10:11.821
If you can handle
this mess alone
then so can I!

10:11.821 --> 10:13.032
Take a break, Gloria.

10:13.032 --> 10:14.033
You deserve it.

10:14.033 --> 10:15.034
Cricket, no!

10:15.034 --> 10:17.117
I've got work to do.

10:17.117 --> 10:19.369
-[all shouting]
-If anyone needs anything,

10:19.369 --> 10:21.371
come to me!

10:21.371 --> 10:24.083
Better hurry.
Parade will be here any second.

10:24.083 --> 10:26.506
[people shouting louder]

10:27.917 --> 10:30.130
Parade? What are you... ?

10:30.130 --> 10:32.051
Huh?

10:32.051 --> 10:34.424
[sweeping orchestral music
playing]

10:34.424 --> 10:36.306
[gasps]

10:36.306 --> 10:39.139
♪♪

10:39.139 --> 10:41.100
My first Parade Day.

10:41.100 --> 10:43.353
It's amazing!

10:43.353 --> 10:45.685
Happy Parade Day to all!

10:45.685 --> 10:48.608
Bow to your queen!

10:48.608 --> 10:51.151
Happy Parade Day,
Miss Splish.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.822
Thanks, Cricket.

10:52.822 --> 10:54.944
[panting] Has anyone
seen my daughter?!

10:54.944 --> 10:57.277
Oh, gosh, Tilly,
where'd you go?!

10:57.277 --> 10:59.279
Tilly?!

11:02.041 --> 11:04.704
[Cricket]
You've all been gathered here
for a once-in-a-lifetime chance

11:04.704 --> 11:07.417
to witness a revelation
in modern agriculture.

11:07.417 --> 11:09.879
Behold, the carrot sucker!

11:09.879 --> 11:12.752
In just three seconds flat,
all the carrots you see here

11:12.752 --> 11:14.384
will be slurped
out of the ground!

11:14.384 --> 11:16.926
Count with me! One!

11:16.926 --> 11:18.428
[clunk]

11:18.428 --> 11:19.889
Two!

11:19.889 --> 11:21.931
Remy, was that sass
or just ignorance?

11:21.931 --> 11:24.724
Cricket, what in the world
did you do?

11:24.724 --> 11:25.855
It's not my fault, dad.

11:25.855 --> 11:27.437
What kind of vacuum clogs
from too much dirt

11:27.437 --> 11:29.769
Well,
this is definitely broken.

11:29.769 --> 11:31.521
Who are you going to call
to fix it, Mr. Green?

11:31.521 --> 11:34.814
Call? [laughs]
I'm not going to call anyone.

11:34.814 --> 11:37.987
I'll fix it myself.
Remy, I'm a DIY guy.

11:37.987 --> 11:40.079
D... I... Y.

11:40.079 --> 11:41.911
It stands for "do it yourself."

11:41.911 --> 11:44.324
Don't your folks ever
fix stuff around the house?

11:44.324 --> 11:46.586
Mnh-mnh.
My family just uses money.

11:46.586 --> 11:47.707
Like this.

11:50.790 --> 11:51.921
I got you a present.

11:51.921 --> 11:54.334
Just a little something
for the house.

11:54.334 --> 11:57.927
Uh, thanks, but, Remy,
I'm concerned you don't possess

11:57.927 --> 12:00.800
the all-important skill
of self-reliance.

12:00.800 --> 12:04.264
Oh, geez, Tilly, dad's doing
his self-reliance speech again.

12:04.264 --> 12:05.845
- Huh?
- I can't hear it

12:05.845 --> 12:08.848
'cause I died of boredom.
[grunts]

12:08.848 --> 12:11.060
[laughs]
Oh, no, it's catching!

12:11.060 --> 12:12.482
[grunts]

12:12.482 --> 12:13.983
Ah, don't listen to them, Remy.

12:13.983 --> 12:16.195
Back in the country,
I learned to be self-reliant.

12:16.195 --> 12:17.617
And being self-reliant
gives you

12:17.617 --> 12:19.619
a sense of pride
and accomplishment.

12:19.619 --> 12:20.910
Take me, for example.

12:20.910 --> 12:23.072
I grow my own food,
change my own oil.

12:23.072 --> 12:24.784
Heck, I even cut my own hair.

12:26.496 --> 12:28.628
[clears throat]
It'll grow out.

12:28.628 --> 12:31.000
Wow,
I wish I could do all that.

12:31.000 --> 12:32.962
Well, you can.
And I'll teach you.

12:32.962 --> 12:35.004
We're going to fix
this vacuum ourselves.

12:35.004 --> 12:37.006
You'll never need to ask
for help again.

12:37.006 --> 12:38.638
- Hooray!
- Let's go!

12:38.638 --> 12:41.140
- Carry me!
- Y-- what?

12:41.140 --> 12:44.594
You don't expect me to walk
there all by myself, do you?

12:44.594 --> 12:46.846
This is going to be harder
than I thought.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.481
Fixing the vacuum
will be easy.

12:51.481 --> 12:52.732
The brush head isn't spinning,

12:52.732 --> 12:55.024
which means we just need
a new vacuum belt.

12:55.024 --> 12:56.986
Hello, sir,
welcome to Overhauls,

12:56.986 --> 12:59.028
the Scandinavian
hardware store.

12:59.028 --> 13:00.069
If you need anything,

13:00.069 --> 13:02.492
ask someone wearing
one of these uniforms.

13:02.492 --> 13:05.074
[laughs] No.

13:05.074 --> 13:06.536
I was literally born

13:06.536 --> 13:08.288
in the plumbing section
of a hardware store.

13:08.288 --> 13:10.750
I think I know
my way around.

13:10.750 --> 13:14.504
Come on, kids, let's find
a door we can open ourselves.

13:14.504 --> 13:16.716
[gasps]

13:16.716 --> 13:19.419
[all] Wow.

13:19.419 --> 13:22.221
This sure is a lot bigger than
the hardware store back home.

13:22.221 --> 13:24.263
How are we ever going to
find anything here?

13:24.263 --> 13:27.767
Use your eyes, Remy.
Look to the signs.

13:27.767 --> 13:30.690
"Kyckling."
"Kotbular."

13:30.690 --> 13:33.933
Huh. No matter.
We'll find it regardless.

13:33.933 --> 13:35.395
Let's go, Remy.

13:35.395 --> 13:37.317
No, no, don't say anything.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.988
I knew it was wrong
when I got in.

13:38.988 --> 13:41.110
[yelps]

13:41.110 --> 13:42.612
- Come on.
- [whimpers]

13:42.612 --> 13:44.364
Geez Louise.

13:44.364 --> 13:47.537
Todd? Todd?
Hey, I'm talking to you!

13:47.537 --> 13:49.038
- Who, me?
- Yeah, you.

13:49.038 --> 13:50.750
You're late for your shift,
Todd.

13:50.750 --> 13:52.662
At least you wore
your uniform this time.

13:52.662 --> 13:53.713
My uniform?

13:53.713 --> 13:55.915
[grunts] Whew.

13:55.915 --> 13:58.337
I<i> am</i> wearing overalls.

13:58.337 --> 14:00.720
Therefore, I work here.

14:00.720 --> 14:03.763
Todd, I need you
on the forklift today.

14:03.763 --> 14:05.635
Forklift?

14:05.635 --> 14:08.848
Bingo bango!

14:08.848 --> 14:11.020
Come on, kids,
if you're not paying attention

14:11.020 --> 14:13.352
to where you're going,
you could get lost in here.

14:13.352 --> 14:16.185
Garden gnomes?
Yes, please.

14:16.185 --> 14:17.977
[grunts]

14:17.977 --> 14:21.190
I can't reach it.
I guess I'll just go home.

14:21.190 --> 14:23.533
And I won't even have
that thing!

14:23.533 --> 14:24.744
[sighs]

14:24.744 --> 14:26.946
Who's going to help
that poor man?

14:26.946 --> 14:29.829
What brave soul
will answer this call?

14:29.829 --> 14:31.411
Me. It'll be me. I will.

14:31.411 --> 14:33.793
[grunting]

14:36.165 --> 14:37.997
Whoa, my thing.

14:39.919 --> 14:41.300
Who<i> was</i> that?

14:41.300 --> 14:43.382
And that's the difference
between male

14:43.382 --> 14:44.964
and female plug-ins.

14:44.964 --> 14:46.636
I have so many questions.

14:46.636 --> 14:48.968
We all do.
Hold on just a minute, Remy.

14:48.968 --> 14:52.432
We need to figure out
where were going-- what the?

14:52.432 --> 14:56.395
Ooh, Vacuumbas!
The robot vacuum!

14:56.395 --> 14:58.568
Hey, Mr. Green,
if you buy one of these,

14:58.568 --> 15:00.319
you won't need
to fix your vacuum.

15:00.319 --> 15:03.402
- My family has like 12 of them.
- [stammers]

15:03.402 --> 15:08.117
Wha-- wha-- wha--
where in the heck are we?

15:08.117 --> 15:10.159
- Mr. Green!
- Huh?

15:10.159 --> 15:12.371
I think this one
likes you!

15:12.371 --> 15:15.034
Remy, put that mechanical
disgrace away.

15:15.034 --> 15:18.037
The vacuum belt's gotta be...
this way.

15:18.037 --> 15:19.088
[panting]

15:21.170 --> 15:23.633
Whee!

15:23.633 --> 15:25.675
No hands!

15:25.675 --> 15:28.007
Going up, going down.

15:28.007 --> 15:29.759
- What's this do?
- [horn beeps]

15:29.759 --> 15:31.180
Oh, excuse me.

15:31.180 --> 15:33.182
Tag, you're it. [laughs]

15:33.182 --> 15:36.936
Whoo! Yee-ha!
This is the best!

15:39.188 --> 15:40.940
Todd,
you got work in aisle 20.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.271
If you're goofing around,

15:42.271 --> 15:44.113
I'll get someone else
to drive the forklift.

15:44.113 --> 15:45.444
Sure thing, boss.

15:45.444 --> 15:49.238
[Tilly] The shoppers
with their tiny arms

15:49.238 --> 15:52.662
reach up to the sky in need.

15:52.662 --> 15:54.664
This store needs a hero.

15:54.664 --> 15:56.125
Huh?

15:56.125 --> 16:00.840
A hero that will climb
the shelves of injustice.

16:00.840 --> 16:05.084
The world looks up and shouts,
"Can someone reach that?!"

16:05.084 --> 16:07.046
And I answer, "Yes."

16:07.046 --> 16:09.298
That's why I am here.

16:09.298 --> 16:13.262
That's why I have become...

16:13.262 --> 16:14.644
Tilly Top Shelf!

16:14.644 --> 16:16.145
[thunder crashes]

16:17.436 --> 16:20.099
Doesn't matter that we got
turned around a bit, Remy.

16:20.099 --> 16:22.732
DIY guys learn
from their mistakes.

16:22.732 --> 16:24.904
I know we're getting close
to the vacuum belts.

16:24.904 --> 16:26.946
I can feel it.

16:26.946 --> 16:28.698
Yeah. Me too.

16:28.698 --> 16:31.410
Should be just
around this corner.

16:31.410 --> 16:33.613
Ah-ha! What?

16:33.613 --> 16:35.705
Hey,
it's the Vacuumbas again.

16:35.705 --> 16:39.168
But we were just--
I don't understand it!

16:39.168 --> 16:41.120
Nothing in this store
makes sense!

16:41.120 --> 16:43.883
First time in a hardware store?
What can I help you find?

16:43.883 --> 16:45.835
[laughs]
First time in a hardware store.

16:45.835 --> 16:48.337
Who does she think she is?
[clears throat]

16:48.337 --> 16:51.260
Remy, do we need help
finding anything?

16:51.260 --> 16:53.262
Oh, yes, we're looking
for a vacuum belt.

16:53.262 --> 16:54.684
Oh, sure thing.
That's in aisle--

16:54.684 --> 16:55.935
Don't listen to her!

16:55.935 --> 16:57.727
I said it's in aisle--

16:57.727 --> 16:59.308
DIY! DIY!

16:59.308 --> 17:01.440
Oh, right.
[screams]

17:01.440 --> 17:05.194
That's it, block out the help,
Remy! Block it out!

17:05.194 --> 17:07.196
Weirdos.

17:07.196 --> 17:10.409
It's gotta be this way!
Come on!

17:10.409 --> 17:13.362
Uh, uh... Mr. Green?

17:13.362 --> 17:15.785
Don't worry, son,
I know where I'm going.

17:15.785 --> 17:17.787
[panting] Wha--

17:17.787 --> 17:19.328
Oh, hello.

17:19.328 --> 17:21.420
Are you looking for
3-inch screws, too?

17:21.420 --> 17:23.042
No, no, we're not.

17:23.042 --> 17:26.005
That's too bad.
We've been looking for a while.

17:26.005 --> 17:28.427
[giggles] We don't need
any help finding them.

17:28.427 --> 17:31.841
Right, Rick? Rick?

17:31.841 --> 17:34.804
- [both scream]
- Bye, now!

17:36.305 --> 17:38.938
Mr. Green,
can't we ask for help now?

17:38.938 --> 17:42.181
No! DIY asks means never
asking for help!

17:42.181 --> 17:44.273
[pants]

17:44.273 --> 17:45.394
Hmm?

17:45.394 --> 17:48.738
[gasps]
Oh, my gosh, there it is.

17:48.738 --> 17:50.189
We did it!

17:50.189 --> 17:52.822
All right, concrete's ready.
Load 'em up.

17:52.822 --> 17:55.575
Watch and learn, fellow
employees.

17:55.575 --> 17:58.407
Hmm, let's see.
♪ Do do do do do ♪

17:58.407 --> 18:00.409
This one.

18:00.409 --> 18:02.291
What are you doing, Todd?!

18:02.291 --> 18:03.623
Ugh, just a second now.

18:03.623 --> 18:05.665
[screams]

18:07.667 --> 18:09.709
Hold on, that's not
what I meant to do.

18:09.709 --> 18:11.881
I can fix this!
[screams]

18:14.714 --> 18:17.476
Ooh, sorry about that.
Oh, my gosh!

18:17.476 --> 18:19.218
What have you done?!

18:19.218 --> 18:22.221
[all exclaiming]

18:22.221 --> 18:25.224
Oh, mercy, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry!

18:25.224 --> 18:28.277
My legs!
I can't move my legs!

18:28.277 --> 18:31.611
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!
Do you feel this, Remy?

18:31.611 --> 18:33.532
Do you feel the self-reliance?!

18:33.532 --> 18:35.364
Wow, you were right.

18:35.364 --> 18:36.495
You don't need anyone's help
ever!

18:36.495 --> 18:37.657
- [crashing]
- Huh?

18:37.657 --> 18:40.039
Watch out, Mr. Green!

18:40.039 --> 18:42.291
What's was that, Remy?
Huh? What?

18:47.627 --> 18:50.880
Sweet porcelain mother.
[yelps]

18:50.880 --> 18:53.803
Mr. Green! Don't worry!
I'll be right there!

18:53.803 --> 18:56.345
Actually,
I'll be right here!

18:56.345 --> 18:59.679
No worries, Remy,
there's no situation

18:59.679 --> 19:02.351
too tough for a DIY g--
[yelps]

19:02.351 --> 19:05.765
I'll call for help!
Help! Help! Help!

19:05.765 --> 19:09.318
It's no use.
My little voice, it won't carry.

19:09.318 --> 19:12.822
I can't do it.
But Mr. Green can.

19:12.822 --> 19:14.904
Mr. Green,
you have to call for help!

19:14.904 --> 19:16.235
It's the only way!

19:16.235 --> 19:19.118
Call for help, Mr. Green!

19:19.118 --> 19:20.329
No, never!

19:20.329 --> 19:22.331
Mr. Green, please!

19:22.331 --> 19:25.705
A DIY guy doesn't need help!

19:25.705 --> 19:29.458
That's ridiculous!
Everybody needs help sometimes!

19:29.458 --> 19:32.291
It might be giants shelf
full of falling toilets

19:32.291 --> 19:33.342
or you need some assistance

19:33.342 --> 19:35.094
getting into your onesie
at night,

19:35.094 --> 19:36.555
but when life's
too overwhelming,

19:36.555 --> 19:39.508
it's nice to know you don't
have to tackle it alone!

19:41.470 --> 19:42.511
[grunts] Yelp.

19:42.511 --> 19:44.974
That's it, Mr. Green. Louder.

19:44.974 --> 19:46.515
Yelp?

19:46.515 --> 19:47.767
More pathetic!

19:47.767 --> 19:49.568
Help.

19:49.568 --> 19:51.771
Shriller!
Like a wounded animal!

19:55.695 --> 19:57.777
Help!! Help!!

19:57.777 --> 20:00.870
I... m needed.

20:00.870 --> 20:02.912
- [thunder crashes]
- Help!

20:02.912 --> 20:06.495
[sighs] My joy ride
turned into a sad ride.

20:06.495 --> 20:09.088
I caused so much destruction
with this small machine.

20:09.088 --> 20:11.460
If only there was some way
to make up for it all.

20:11.460 --> 20:12.712
[Mr. Green] Help!!

20:12.712 --> 20:16.295
Oh, my gosh, was that dad?
I'm coming for you, dad!

20:16.295 --> 20:18.928
Help!!

20:18.928 --> 20:20.930
[screams]

20:20.930 --> 20:22.762
[grunts]

20:22.762 --> 20:24.473
Tilly! Huh?

20:24.473 --> 20:25.895
[bellows]

20:28.347 --> 20:31.440
Huh?
I'm alive! I'm alive!

20:31.440 --> 20:34.353
[laughs] Tilly, Tilly, oh,
my sweet daughter, come here.

20:34.353 --> 20:36.065
Remy, you saved me.

20:36.065 --> 20:38.197
We did it together,
Mr. Green!

20:38.197 --> 20:40.449
You wonderful children,
look at you.

20:40.449 --> 20:42.571
Now where's my son?!

20:42.571 --> 20:44.994
I'm right here, dad!
Come here, big guy!

20:48.207 --> 20:49.789
[shelves crashing]

20:57.716 --> 20:59.678
Huh, can't believe
we went through so much trouble

20:59.678 --> 21:02.181
- for such a little part.
- Ooh, ooh!

21:02.181 --> 21:04.433
- Can I fix it, Mr. Green?
- Sure thing!

21:04.433 --> 21:06.515
You know, Remy,
you showed me that sometimes

21:06.515 --> 21:07.686
it's okay to ask for help.

21:07.686 --> 21:10.439
Now I've got a new policy
on self-reliance.

21:10.439 --> 21:14.193
Always DIY
unless you're about to DI-die.

21:14.193 --> 21:15.354
- I'm all done.
- [vacuum whirs]

21:15.354 --> 21:17.026
Well, looks good to me.

21:17.026 --> 21:21.951
Mr. Green, I think I feel it.
The power of self-reliance.

21:21.951 --> 21:24.033
We can do anything!

21:24.033 --> 21:26.075
[sputtering]

21:26.075 --> 21:27.957
Remy, can you call
the repair man?

21:27.957 --> 21:28.958
One step ahead of you.

21:30.960 --> 21:33.372
<i> ♪ I got sweat in my eyes ♪</i>

21:33.372 --> 21:36.966
<i> ♪ Lost a bet
and got bit by 100 flies ♪</i>

21:36.966 --> 21:40.419
<i> ♪ I fell out
a big old tree ♪</i>

21:40.419 --> 21:43.012
<i> ♪ Hit every branch
and scraped up both my knees ♪</i>

21:43.012 --> 21:45.514
<i> ♪ I got chased by dogs ♪</i>

21:45.514 --> 21:46.555
<i> ♪ Bit by a frog ♪</i>

21:46.555 --> 21:48.517
<i> ♪ Got a rash on my leg ♪</i>

21:48.517 --> 21:50.810
<i> ♪ Dropped a dozen eggs ♪</i>

21:50.810 --> 21:54.103
<i> ♪ I got splinters
since 7 to 10:00 ♪</i>

21:54.103 --> 21:56.605
<i> ♪ And tomorrow,
I'll do it all again ♪</i>
